Scenario: Success Create Hazard Report and Complete Follow-up Task


  Given the user opens the Hazard menu in the Mobile App
  Then the Hazard page shows the list of existing hazard reports

  When the user taps the Report Hazard or New Hazard button
  Then the app opens the Hazard Reporting Form

  When the user selects a Location
  Then the dropdown opens and the user can select one location, and the selected value appears

  When the user selects a Sublocation
  Then the dropdown opens and the user can select one sublocation, and the selected value appears

  When the user selects an Area
  Then the dropdown opens and the user can select one area, and the selected value appears

  When the user inputs an Area Description
  Then the text field accepts the input and may be left empty

  When the user taps the Evidence Image Picker
  Then the camera or gallery opens

  When the user captures or chooses an image
  Then the image preview is added to the Evidence field

  When the user selects the PIC
  Then the PIC field is automatically pre-filled with the reporter's name

  When the user submits the Hazard report
  Then the request is sent to the server and the system generates a hazard entry and a follow-up task

  Then the PIC receives a notification for the follow-up task
  And all users in the same area receive a hazard alert notification

  When the PIC opens the Follow-up Task assigned to them
  Then the task details screen appears

  When the PIC visits the location and opens the Submit Follow-up screen
  Then the follow-up submission form appears

  When the PIC adds Evidence using the Image Picker
  Then the camera or gallery opens

  When the PIC selects the Resolution Date using the DateTime Picker
  Then the DateTime picker opens and the selected date and time appear correctly

  When the PIC taps the (+) button to add Co Observers
  Then the system adds additional Select fields for more observers

  When the PIC selects one or more Co Observers
  Then the chosen observers appear as selected entries

  When the PIC submits the follow-up task
  Then the follow-up is successfully submitted to the server

  Then the Direct Supervisor of the Area receives a notification indicating follow-up completion
